<p>METHOD:</p>

<p>Smash the ripe banana at the bottom of the mug then add in the honey, coconut oil and almond milk and combine well </p>

<p>Add in the oat or regular flour, baking powder and cinnamon and stir well </p>

<p>Top with walnuts and place in the microwave to cook on high for three minutes</p>

<p>Eat and enjoy</p>

<p>Source: TikTok</p>

<p>Since publishing the video online on July 28, it has gone viral and been viewed more than 90,000 times. </p>

<p>Hundreds of TikTok users were impressed with the simplicity of the meal and seemed eager to try make it for themselves.</p>

<p>'Trying this tonight, thanks!' one man said.</p>

<p>'Can you use normal flour instead of oar flour?' a woman asked, and Ayeh said: 'Of course!'</p>

<p>A third added: 'You are really good at cooking.' </p>
